{
  "question_id": "77c3eab0-280f-4782-ada1-86f630e20f4a",
  "short_text": "Pyramid - 5",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Pyramid** of `2 * N - 1` rows using pluses (`+`) and hashes (`#`).\n\nThe last column of the pyramid contains hashes (`#`), and the remaining columns contain pluses (`+`).\n\n````\n        #\n      + #\n    + + #\n  + + + #\n+ + + + #\n  + + + #\n    + + #\n      + #\n        #\n````\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every plus (`+`) and every hash (`#`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `2 * N - 1` rows containing pluses (`+`) and hashes (`#`) as a **Pyramid** shown in the sample output. \n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`, \n\n- Print pluses (`+`) and hashes (`#`) on **9** rows (`(2 * 5) - 1`) as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-pyramid-5.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Plus in the box indicates the plus and a space (\"+ \")\n- The Hash in the box indicates the hash and a space (\"# \")\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n\nThe output should be,\n\n````\n        #\n      + #\n    + + #\n  + + + #\n+ + + + #\n  + + + #\n    + + #\n      + #\n        #\n````",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "0eb8dce9-93cd-41cb-aa1b-941c5b103306",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number + 1):\n    spaces = \"  \" * (number - each_number)\n    symbols = \"+ \" * (each_number - 1) + \"#\"\n\n    each_row = spaces + symbols\n    print(each_row)\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number):\n    spaces = \"  \" * each_number\n    symbols = \"+ \" * ((number - each_number) - 1) + \"#\"\n\n    each_row = spaces + symbols\n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
